reut2-017.sgm, U.S. GULF OF MEXICO RIG COUNT CLIMBS TO 38.9 PCT, Utilization of offshore mobile rigs inthe Gulf of Mexico climbed by 2.1 pct last week to 38.9 pct,reflecting a total of 91 working rigs, Offshore Data Servicessaid.    One year ago, the Gulf of Mexico utilization rate was 32.5pct. Offshore Data Services said some drilling contractors hadreported recent increases of about 1,000 dlrs a day on largejackup rigs, which now command rates of 11,000 to 12,000 dlrs aday.    In the European/Mediterranean area the rig utilization raterose 0.6 pct to 53.6 pct, against 67.3 pct one year ago.    Worldwide rig utilization rose by 1.2 pct to 57.7 pct,reflecting a net increase of eight working rigs. Offshore DataServices said a total of 419 rigs were in use worldwide and 307were idled last week. Reuter&#3;
